The paper focuses on the performance evaluation of monitoring and information services for distributed systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The study also involves network communication and data management, which are relevant to Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of the three monitoring services, which could be relevant to the sub-category of Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed). Finally, the study involves experiments and performance evaluation, which could be relevant to Performance (cs.PF).
